==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Buttonmold
<hw>But"ton*mold`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A disk of
bone, wood, or other material, which is made into a button by covering
it with cloth.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>buttonmould</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Fossil buttonmolds</b></col>, <cd>joints of encrinites.
See <er>Encrinite</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Buttons</ent>⟦br⟧
